  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Accuracy of [F-18]-FCH PET/MRI in localization of diseased parathyroid gland</measure>
    <time_frame>1 month postoperatively</time_frame>
    <description>Value of [F-18]-FCH PET/MRI next to Ultrasound of the Neck and 99mTc-MIBI SPECT/CT in determining which of the four parathyroid glands
Reference standards:
Intra-operative location of the hyper functioning gland by inspection and post-operative pathological confirmation.
Determination of biochemical cure per usual standard of care: intraoperative PTH and calcium and PTH postoperatively.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
